# Git commits

**Format:** `type(scope): description [AI]`

- Imperative, lowercase description, no trailing period
- **Total length ≤ 72** (includes `type(scope): ` and ` [AI]`)
- Always use suffix `[AI]` when the agent creates the commit

**Types:** `feat` · `fix` · `hotfix` · `refactor` · `test` · `docs` · `chore` · `style`

## When committing

1. Inspect `git status` and staged diff (`git diff --staged`, else `git diff`)
2. Propose one message for all staged changes
3. If diff **≤ 400 lines:** confirm then commit
4. If diff **> 400 lines:** warn; suggest split commits by feature/file group; let user pick group or single commit

## Pre-commit checks

- No debug `console.log` / `dd()` left in diff
- No commented-out dead code blocks
- No credentials in source
- Changes match branch scope

See also root `commit.md` and `commitlint.config.js`.
